x4freetext: HI-13 tandem accelerator in China
Institute of Atomic Energy.
A collimated 9Be beam, the current range was 50-200
enA(electrical nA). Charge of incident ion is 3+.
The 208Pb and 209Bi targets with the thickness of
about 150 microgram/cm2 evaporated on nearly 25
microgram/cm2 carbon foil backings.
The experimental data were analyzed by the code of
PTOLEMY. The parameters of the optical potential have
been extracted by the phenomenological optical model
analysis.
Overall absolute angle accuracy is estimated
to be 0.02 degree.

x4freetext: Total uncertainty is given.
The measured data shown in Fig2 and Fig3 were the
ratios of the measured differential cross sections
to those for Rutherford scattering.
The beam energy 37.6 MeV in Fig2 and Fig3 is wrong
affirmed by the first author, it should be 37.8 MeV.
All measured data are shown in Fig2 and Fig3
Experimental data were received from the first author
on 20/05/2011, and confirmed the uncertainty is total
uncertainty.
